❯ 1. Web — vanilla JS + Canvas
     Plain HTML5 Canvas + JS/TS, no framework. Lightest setup, easy to host as a static site.
  2. Web — React + Canvas/PixiJS
     React shell with a Canvas or PixiJS game layer. Good if you want UI (menus, stats, sharing) plus a game canvas.
  3. Web — game engine (Phaser)
     Phaser 3 handles sprites, physics, input, scenes out of the box. Fastest path to a polished arcade feel.





